physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Indurated ulcer of 1 cm in diameter and 1 cm in depth adjacent to the penile corona, firm and nontender; small, mobile, nontender left inguinal nodes palpated; BCG scar present on the arm; normal findings on examination of other systems.
The woman appeared healthy; whitish, odorless vaginal discharge with some cervical ulceration; negative results for urine dipstick test; normal chest radiography findings.
